data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
Live updates, news and TV schedules for the 2024 Paris Olympic Games, with womens basketball and womens volleyball taking center stage Sunday.

Over the weekend people as far as Hermosa and Redondo Beach, roughly 8 to 9 miles away from Inglewoods Hollywood Park, heard the pulsing of music being played at the HARD Summer music festival.

Outdated gray vinyl floors are the object of ridicule, but the trend still fills rental units across L.A.

One Long Beach group is turning dead urban trees into usable lumber, while planting new saplings and providing work for the people society has left behind.

Southern California musical all-stars Billie Eilish, the Red Hot Chili Peppers and Snoop Dogg will be featured during the Olympic closing ceremony.

Over-tourism backlash: In Instragram-favorite cities and towns across Europe, some residents have reached their limit with massive crowds of tourists.
